agent.marketingAbout: Vivian is a second generation Texan, born in Austin while her dad was a professor at UT Austin. Her family moved to other parts of the country and Vivian returned to Texas ten years ago, making Leander home. Before becoming a realtor, Vivian was a commercial insurance agent and broker. Vivian represents buyers, investors and sellers of residential real estate. She also has experience in property management, investing and remodeling. These skills along with her knowledge of Austin's real estate market help her provide outstanding service that each buyer and seller deserves. Vivian is passionate about the needs and goals of her clients and strives to give them exceptional service.

single.description: Welcome to 725 Arrowood Pl. This is a wonderful 4-bedroom, 2.5-bathroom home tucked away in a friendly cul-de-sac in the popular Sonoma community of vibrant Round Rock. There is an ample covered front porch to relax on. Upon entry, warm wood laminate flooring and a cozy and welcoming atmosphere greet you. A versatile front room graces the entrance, ready to adapt to your needs, be it a formal dining room, a home office, bonus room. The heart of the home, the kitchen, features sleek quartz counters, custom backsplash, stainless steel appliances, and a gas range. The living area, adorned with a stunning fireplace, presents a perfect space to make memories. There is a second dining area next to the kitchen. There is a half bathroom downstairs. The upstairs holds four bedrooms. The primary suite boasts a peaceful primary bedroom and an expansive bathroom with dual vanities, a separate tub, separate shower, and a generous walk-in closet with custom inserts. All of the major items have been replaced in the last 4 years! New roof, water heater, HVAC, windows, appliances, fence. See the extensive list of features and updates. No carpet and very low tax rate of 1.7541! You'll love what the community offers - two pools, two playgrounds, scenic ponds, and walking trails to unwind. In an excellent location near highways, close to Kalahari Resort, Dell Diamond and employers like Samsung, Tesla and Dell. Acclaimed RRISD schools and Round Rock's title as America's number one city to live in, it truly is an incredible find.
